Rayna Cottrell Stewart II (born June 18, 1973) is an American former professional football safety who is the assistant special teams coach for the Tennessee Titans of the National Football League (NFL). He played five seasons for the Houston/Tennessee Oilers, Miami Dolphins, and Jacksonville Jaguars. He was selected by the Houston Oilers in the fifth round of the 1996 NFL draft with the 143rd overall pick.
